						               													<description>Each player (blue: locksmith, red: butcher, green: farmer, black: salesman) starts with a workgroup of 4 workers at the starting point B of their color. Movement is determined by a die. On the roll of a 1 the player puts a worker on the space of his color of the employment exchange (Arbeitsamt) and rolls again. If a worker gets on a corner space (factory, butchery, farmland, department store)with doesn't fit his profession, he has to return to the employment exchange. If a worker would get on an occupied space and the player occupying this space shouts: &amp;quot;Kleiner Mann was nun?&amp;quot; the arriving worker is returned to the employment exchange. If the other player isn't paying attention, his worker goes to the employment exchange.  &amp;#10;If a worker gets on a space labor service (Arbeitsdienst)of another color, the player loses 3 turns. On a space of his color, he may immediately roll 3 times. If a worker lands on the train he advances 12 spaces or 6 spaces if he lands on the ship.&amp;#10;A worker who reaches the last white space in front of the employment exchange space of his color, enters space C of his color. The first player to get his whole workgroup into space C of his color wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
